isDataValid

boolean isDataValid(java.lang.String dataID)
Query method for validity of table data.

Parameters:
dataID - String to identify one data member
Returns:
true, if data member valid

Description:
Overlaoded method to query the validity of one table data member.
With each query, one table data member can be checked if it is read from the transponder. The transferred dataID contains a string for data identification.

verifyDataBlocks

int verifyDataBlocks(int blockNr,
                     int blockCnt)
Method for verify received with sent transponder data block(s).

Parameters:
blockNr - first number of data block
blockCnt - number of blocks to be verified
Returns:
Fedm.OK or an error code (<0)

Description:
Some tables have separate memories for received and transmit data. This allows the verification of sent with received transponder data.
This method verifies only complete data blocks.
If the content of the data blocks are equal, then the method returns Fedm.OK, otherwise Fedm.ERROR_VERIFY.
If an error occurs, method returns an error code (<0).

verifyDataBytes

int verifyDataBytes(int startByte,
                    int byteCnt)
Method for verify received with sent transponder data byte(s).

Parameters:
startByte - - first byte
byteCnt - - number of bytes to be verified
Returns:
Fedm.OK or an error code (<0)

Description:
Some tables (e.g. FedmIsoTableItem) have separate memories for received and transmit data. This allows the verification of sent with received transponder data.
This method verifies data bytes without the limitation of the blocksize.
If the content of the data bytes are equal, then the method returns Fedm.OK, otherwise Fedm.ERROR_VERIFY.
If an error occurs, the lastError attribute is set and the method returns an error code (<0).

getIdentifier

java.lang.String getIdentifier()
Method for table identification

Returns:
identification string

Description:
Method returns a string like 'ISO' or 'BRM' to identify a table.
